{"id": "EUVD-2025-11226", "enisaUuid": "05bfecb1-e9f1-3693-960c-92107b9c8c25", "description": "In the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\nexfat: fix missing shutdown check\n\nxfstests generic/730 test failed because after deleting the device\nthat still had dirty data, the file could still be read without\nreturning an error. The reason is the missing shutdown check in\n->read_iter.\n\nI also noticed that shutdown checks were missing from ->write_iter,\n->splice_read, and ->mmap. This commit adds shutdown checks to all\nof them.", "datePublished": "2025-04-16T15:34:42", "dateUpdated": "2025-10-31T21:30:55", "baseScore": 0.0, "references": ["https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2025-22076", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/47e35366bc6fa3cf189a8305bce63992495f3efa", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/4a9595eb024b8319957c178be3cdeed613ac0795", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/539147585ca453db6e3d7a5cf3b9c9690513762d", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/e41e33eb795cb9c1ead6ac627d8710546fac6e81"], "aliases": ["CVE-2025-22076", "GHSA-6c74-8p8j-4qv8"], "assigner": "Linux", "epss": 0.02, "enisaIdProduct": [{"id": "0acf07a6-f164-3e3c-8e7d-be1431a6f1ec", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.12.23"}, {"id": "1ff2f833-8ddb-36b1-abb1-f373f6c20d11", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 0"}, {"id": "282bb95d-c4b8-3c8a-9b64-c12bddd3c471", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "f761fcdd289d07e8547fef7ac76c3760fc7803f2 <47e35366bc6fa3cf189a8305bce63992495f3efa"}, {"id": "4842d959-a351-36c8-9482-7c0ce3f54c73", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.15-rc1"}, {"id": "6d363cd5-a1c5-3863-b355-4e7dbf327673", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "f761fcdd289d07e8547fef7ac76c3760fc7803f2 <539147585ca453db6e3d7a5cf3b9c9690513762d"}, {"id": "7386fece-8bab-35d5-906e-cf14abb5b490", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.13.11"}, {"id": "7d397ba2-55c2-3d6f-88a3-378a301